OL,6,FHowever, in April 2024, the island's
OL,7,FPolicy and Resources Committee put
OL,8,Fforward a proposition to suspend the
OL,9,Fpolicy, after it was claimed that
OL,10,Fdevelopments were not sufficiently
OL,11,Fprofitable or feasible, and as a
OL,12,Fresult, argued the rule was a barrier
OL,13,Fto getting spades in the ground.
