OL,3,CCould a tax on new homes fund more
OL,4,C'affordable housing' in Guernsey?
OL,6,F"In terms of the GP11 mechanism in
OL,7,Fitself as a policy, we support the
OL,8,Fneed for a contribution to be made
OL,9,Ftowards social housing and affordable
OL,10,Fhousing, the issue was around the
OL,11,Fimplementation and the uncertainty
OL,12,Fthat GP11 brought."
OL,14,FThe demand for affordable homes has
OL,15,Fbeen widely discussed on the island
OL,16,Ffor a number of years.
OL,18,FIt was labelled as "an appalling
OL,19,Fsituation" by Deputy Peter Roffey in
OL,20,F2023, after no new social housing
OL,21,Funits were built during that year.
